===Etymology===
Unclear. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} lists several proposals:
* related to {{cog|bo|ཆབ||water}} ({{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986)}}), yet initial velars do not palatize in Written Tibetan;
* related to {{cog|kac|tr=məgyep|t=liquor}};
* related to {{cog|my|ချိပ်||lac}}, {{cog|tbq-lol-pro|*C-gripᴸ||lac; pine}} ({{zh-ref|Peiros & Starostin, 1996}}, STEDT), if so from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-kryap||bug, ant, cochineal, lac insect}} (whence also {{och-l|蠟}} "wax");

Likely related to {{och-l|湆}} & {{och-l|協}} ({{och-l|汁}}'s dialectal synonym attested east of {{w|Tong Pass}}); yet not to {{och-l|瀋||liquid, juice}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

; Hong Kong Cantonese "source"
: {{sl|yue|en|sauce}}.

